article.headline: Green Bay 77, Houston Baptist 61
article.story: GREEN BAY, Wis. -- Jarvis Williams grabbed a double-double, scoring 14 points and pulling down a career-high 12 rebounds as Wisconsin-Green Bay beat Houston Baptist 77-61 on Monday night. Daniel Turner and Rahmon Fletcher also scored 14 points each for the Phoenix (7-9), who were coming off two straight losses, while Alec Brown helped out with a double-double of his own, scoring 12 points and grabbing 10 rebounds. The Phoenix led the whole way and were up by as many as 20 points midway through the second half. They shot 42.4 percent from the field, including 53.6 percent after intermission. Andrew Gonzalez led the game in scoring with 29 points for the Huskies (1-11), which shot 38.3 percent from the field. Michael Moss added 17 points for Houston Baptist.
